    "Mechanism_of_Action": {
      "text": "Highly selective, oral potassium removing agent\nNon-absorbed zirconium silicate that captures potassium in exchange for hydrogen and sodium\nIncreases fecal potassium excretion through binding K+ in GI tract",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Comments": {
      "text": "Onset of action at 1.0 hour and median time to achieving normal potassium levels at 2.2 hours, with 92% achieving normal potassium within 48 hours.\nNot used as an emergency treatment for life threatening hyperkalemia due to delayed onset of action\nAvailable at Harbor-UCLA, but not yet widely available in the community\nIf asked by nephrology to give Kayexalate, kindly suggest Lokelma instead",
